  Q. Your shot on 9 out of the rough, how treacherous was that shot?  
 SERGIO GARCÃA: The good thing was that it was into the wind, so I knew that I could stop it if I hit it properly. So it wasn't like a full-blooded flop shot because it was a little bit into the wind and I was kind of chipping at the green. If I would have been ten yards farther, then it would have been a bit more difficult.   
  
  Q. Do you feel with the wind down a little bit these first two days that it's necessary to take advantage now while you can?   
 SERGIO GARCÃA: Well, if you can, yes. But it's not an easy course. It doesn't matter, with or without wind, this is a course that you have to place the ball nicely and you have to place it on the right side, you have to place it on the right side of the fairway, then on the greens, and if you're a little bit off, it can make it quite tough for you.   
 So I don't think it's -- people are playing nicely, but it's not that easy.   
  
